When my wrist first broke down a few weeks ago, we went to Ruby Tuesdays that evening. I chose there because I wanted a steak, but as I was looking at the menu, I realized that I couldn’t get a steak unless somebody cut it up for me. That triggered all kinds of other thoughts about what a lame wrist could mean for my future. I broke down and cried right there in the middle of the restaurant.  Gavin asked me if I was crying because the pain. I slowly shook my head no, and then everyone knew exactly why I was crying, which only made it worse.  we had to leave almost as soon as we arrived. We ended up getting pizza that night instead.